name: Pro English
smallText: Proenglish website was created for one English language school. At first glance, this looks like just a regular website, but only at first glance. When we take a closer look, this is actually a full-stack application. Behind the impression of a regular static website, here are some very powerful fetures. This site has a full login system. It also has a dashboard that admins can use to modify the content of a site. Everything will be explained below. Let's start first with the static part.

text.name: p
text.content: Proenglish website was created for one English language school. At first glance, this looks like just a regular website, but only at first glance. When we take a closer look, this is actually a full-stack application. Behind the impression of a regular static website, here are some very powerful fetures. This site has a full login system. It also has a dashboard that admins can use to modify the content of a site. Everything will be explained below. Let's start first with the static part.

text.name: p
text.content: The website consists of seven primary pages. There are six parts to the homepage. The first part is the classic message of welcome.

text.name: p
text.content: The second part is related to a brief introduction of the school with a link to the detailed description.

text.name: p
text.content: The third part is like a billboard or a section where we can find some information related to the placement of isites.

text.name: p
text.content: The fourth part is a shorter version of the blog. Each of the offered blog boxes had a link that takes us to a separate page where we can read blogs in more detail. There is also a newsletter subscription.

text.name: p
text.content: The fifth part is already a bit more complicated than the others and is not a classic statics. Here, users can see the school activity schedule as well as their schedules. In fact this is a very important part of this website. There are also two links that direct us to the events page, where we can see events in more detail

text.name: p
text.content: This is the part where we can briefly read the information related to the professors who are teaching.

text.name: p
text.content: This is a page where you can find detailed information regarding the school. Their principles and ways of working.

text.name: p
text.content: This is a course page. Here we have information related to English language level.

text.name: p
text.content: Below we have a separate text for each level of knowledge. Otherwise, it is a slider with which we manipulate forward/backward arrows. The large rectangle on the right increases or decreases in envy as we go forward or backward. Also the text in the rectangle changes. The text and images on this page come from our database.

text.name: p
text.content: This is the page where we have all the information about all the tests required to obtain certain certifications. On the right we see the names of each exam in a different color. We also have some kind of slider here. When we click on the exam name, the current exam is minimized to the left and the next exam is maximized. We get the effect of leafing through a book. The text on this page come from our database.

text.name: p
text.content: This is a page where we can keep track of all school activities. We have three options. We can watch daily events. We can watch the weekly events, and we can watch the monthly ones. We also have the opportunity to choose any day of the year and see what happened then. We get all the information from the database.

text.name: p
text.content: This is a classic blog site. Here we can watch and read the various news that the school is throwing out.

text.name: p
text.content: By clicking on the link we go to a page where we can read the news in full. Also in the upper margin we have a read indicator. Thick pink line.

text.name: p
text.content: This is the contact page. Here we have implemented google maps api. Here we can see the address where the school is located. We also have an option for google street. There is also a contact form through which we can send the school an email.

text.name: p
text.content: This is the registration page. This page has been shut down for other users. Serves only for site admins. After registration we get a login page

text.name: p
text.content: After registration we get a logging page and after logging in we have access to the dashboard, but we'll talk about that later. Login was done in node js. There is also validation in case we did not enter something properly.

text.name: p
text.content: This is a dashboard. This is where admins can change the content of some pages. We can change blog, events, exams, and about.

text.name: p
text.content: When we click on the edit blog on the menu we get all the current blogs we have. We get two options for each blog, edit and delete. The delete button permanently deletes the blog

text.name: p
text.content: On the edit button, we get old text that we can edit in the editor to a new one. The same procedure is done for exams and about.

text.name: p
text.content: Event insertion is slightly different. We get a panel in the form of a calendar.

text.name: p
text.content: With a double click, we get a window through which to insert an event. Enter title, time and description and on button save we save data on database. We see the events on the right, and in addition we have two icons. One is for editing events and the other is for deleting.

text.name: p
text.content: When we click delete, it pops up a validation pop-up where we need to confirm delete operations. Deletion validation also works for other deletion operations. For edit, we get the same window as for inserting events only this time it lists the event that we need to edit.
